[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Samuel said to all Israel, “I have done"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " everything you requested."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I have given you a king."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now look! This king walks before you. As for me, I am old and gray, though my sons are here with you. I have walked before you from the time of my youth till the present day. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Here I am. Bring a charge against me before the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and before his chosen king."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Whose ox have I taken? Whose donkey have I taken? Whom have I wronged? Whom have I oppressed? From whose hand have I taken a bribe so that I would overlook something? Tell me,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and I will return it to you!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They replied, “You have not wronged us or oppressed us. You have not taken anything from the hand of anyone.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He said to them, “The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is witness against you, and his chosen king"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is witness this day, that you have not found any reason to accuse me.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They said, “He is witness!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Samuel said to the people, “The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is the one who chose Moses and Aaron and who brought your ancestors"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " up from the land of Egypt. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now take your positions, so I may confront you"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " before the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " regarding all the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’s just actions toward you and your ancestors."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When Jacob entered Egypt, your ancestors cried out to the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ". The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sent Moses and Aaron, and they led your ancestors out of Egypt and settled them in this place."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “But they forgot the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " their God, so he gave"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " them into the hand of Sisera, the general in command of Hazor’s"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " army,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and into the hand of the Philistines and into the hand of the king of Moab, and they fought against them. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then they cried out to the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and admitted,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ‘We have sinned, for we have forsaken the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and have served the Baals and the images of Ashtoreth."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now deliver us from the hand of our enemies so that we may serve you.’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sent Jerub-Baal,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Barak,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jephthah, and Samuel,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and he delivered you from the hand of the enemies all around you, and you were able to live securely."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “When you saw that King Nahash of the Ammonites was advancing against you, you said to me, ‘No! A king will rule over us’ – even though the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God is your king! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now look! Here is the king you have chosen – the one that you asked for! Look, the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has given you a king! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " If you fear the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", serving him and obeying him"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and not rebelling against what he says,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and if both you and the king who rules over you follow the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God, all will be well."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But if you don’t obey"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and rebel against what the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " says, the hand of the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " will be against both you and your king."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “So now, take your positions and watch this great thing that the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is about to do in your sight. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Is this not the time of the wheat harvest? I will call on the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so that he makes it thunder and rain. Realize and see what a great sin you have committed before the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by asking for a king for yourselves.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Samuel called to the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", and the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " made it thunder and rain that day. All the people were very afraid of both the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and Samuel. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " All the people said to Samuel, “Pray to the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God on behalf of us – your servants – so we won’t die, for we have added to all our sins by asking for a king.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Samuel said to the people, “Don’t be afraid. You have indeed sinned."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " However, don’t turn aside from the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ". Serve the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with all your heart. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You should not turn aside after empty things that can’t profit and can’t deliver, since they are empty."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " will not abandon his people because he wants to uphold his great reputation."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was pleased to make you his own people. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " As far as I am concerned, far be it from me to sin against the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by ceasing to pray for you! I will instruct you in the way that is good and upright. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " However, fear the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and serve him faithfully with all your heart. Just look at the great things he has done for you! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But if you continue to do evil, both you and your king will be swept away.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]